      • readhead

        protected UUID readhead()
        read the head of the list. Note, this has the effect of inserting the list container object into the read set, but does not put the actual node there. If query_helper returns false, it means we've already read the head in the current transaction, so we're forced to return the most recently observed value.
        Returns:

      • readnext

        Parameters:
        node -
        Returns:
